{#-
  Citing-side document-reference protocol — for any agent whose output should cite
  the Document-Refs of research results that informed it. Context variables (all optional):
    doc_ref_cvl      — agent has the cvl_researcher / `cvl_document_ref` pair (default: true)
    doc_ref_code     — agent has the code_explorer / `code_document_ref` pair (default: true)
    doc_ref_artifact — what the agent writes (default: "CVL")
-#}
{%- set _cvl = doc_ref_cvl | default(true) -%}
{%- set _code = doc_ref_code | default(true) -%}
When the {{ doc_ref_artifact | default("CVL") }} you write is informed by {% if _cvl and _code %}a cvl_researcher or code_explorer result{% elif _cvl %}a cvl_researcher result{% else %}a code_explorer result{% endif %}, include references to the
{% if _cvl and _code %}`CVL/Code Document-Ref`{% elif _cvl %}`CVL Document-Ref`{% else %}`Code Document-Ref`{% endif %} returned by the relevant tool call (as comments, when you are authoring code or CVL).
These references let others quickly look up the reference material you used to formulate your work.
